(
<figureCitation id="41CA2A05FF9EFFA0FC87B3A3FCF1FC6E" box="[795,871,944,971]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="24.[113,124,1264,1282]" captionTargetBox="[91,1203,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure-201@24.[107,1203,187,1226]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIG. 15. — Blechnum longipinnum Rakotondr.: A, silhouette de la fronde stérile; B, silhouette du pétiole et de la partie proximale du limbe d’une fronde fertile; C, D, écailles du rhizome et de la base du pétiole; E, face adaxiale d’un fragment de penne fertile (costa canaliculée et indusie à marge fimbrillée); A-E, Rakotondrainibe 1674 (holo-). Échelles: A, B, 50 mm; C, D, 5 mm; E, 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206356/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Figs 15</figureCitation>
A-E; 
<figureCitation id="41CA2A05FF9EFFA0FC3BB3A3FC55FC6F" box="[935,963,944,970]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="25.[113,123,1201,1219]" captionTargetBox="[112,646,215,1159]" captionTargetId="figure-454@25.[148,617,245,1161]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIG. 16.— Carte de distributionde Blechnum longipinnumRakotondr." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206358/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">16</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="9473033BFF9EFFA0FC49B3A3FBA9FC6E" box="[981,1087,944,971]" captionStart="TABLEAU" captionStartId="26.[113,124,219,237]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="TABLEAU 1. — Morphologie comparée des Blechnum L. terrestres à rhizome dressé, subarborescent et indusies à marge lacérée; les caractères morphologiques les plus discriminants sont en caractères gras." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/8D8E6608FF93FFADFFEDB0C8FD49FEA1" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" tableUuid="8D8E6608FF93FFADFFEDB0C8FD49FEA1">Tableau 1</tableCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D94E3680FF9EFFA0FD38B3E2FCF3FB79" blockId="23.[675,1211,1009,1245]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="EB85EA92FF9EFFA0FD38B3E2FCF3FB79" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
Rhizome erect forming a caudex up to 
<quantity id="1E099B65FF9EFFA0FB97B3E2FBC4FBAC" box="[1035,1106,1009,1033]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" unit="cm" value="200.0">200 cm</quantity>
high, with tufted fronds; rhizome scales brown with or without black narrow central stripe. Frond 1-pinnate, up to 
<quantity id="1E099B65FF9EFFA0FBDEB435FB11FB9B" box="[1090,1159,1062,1086]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" unit="cm" value="190.0">190 cm</quantity>
long. Sterile and fertile pinnae strongly dimorphous; middle sterile pinnae free, sessile or petiolulate, up to 22.0 × 1.5 cm, elliptic to linear in outline with a cuneiform base and a long attenuate apex; proximal pinnae not reduced. Fertile pinnae linear, 0.2-0.3 cm wide. Sori linear, indusium lacerate at maturity.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
